data.enText: the main part of sth; most of sth
The bulk of the population lives in cities.
data.chText: 大多数人口居住在城市里。

data.enText: the (large) size or quantity of sth
Despite its bulk and weight, the car is extremely fast.
data.chText: 尽管这辆车大而且重，速度却非常快。

data.enText: a bulk order (= one for a large number of similar items)
bulk buying (= buying in large amounts, often at a reduced price)
It's cheaper to buy in bulk .
the weight or shape of sb/sth large
data.chText: 巨大的体重（或重量、形状、身体等）

data.enText: She heaved her bulk out of the chair.
data.chText: 她挪动庞大的躯体，费力地从椅子里站起来。

data.enText: to be the most important part of sth
to make sth bigger, thicker or heavier
data.chText: 使某物加大（或加厚、加重）

means: 巨大的体重(或重量、形状、身体等)

ex.enText: What size shoe do you wear?
This apartment is roughly 300 square feet in size.
ex.chText: 这套公寓的面积大约有300平方英尺。

ex.enText: We decreased the size of the group from 15 to 5.
ex.chText: 我们把小组的人数从15人减少到5人。

synonyms.bx: 主要指尺码、规模、面积、身材等的大小，也指数量、数额等的多少。

ex.enText: Great bulk does not always mean great weight.
ex.chText: 体积大并不总是意味着分量重。

ex.enText: It was a document of surprising bulk.
ex.chText: 这是一份篇幅惊人的文件。

synonyms.bx: 不用于准确的度量，只表示相当大的体积或数量。

ex.enText: What are the dimensions of this room?
Width is a linear dimension, too.
ex.chText: 宽度也是一种线性尺寸。

ex.enText: My parents have bought a house of generous dimensions.
ex.chText: 我的父母买了一所宽敞的房屋。

synonyms.bx: 指物体的面积、容积、规模等，通常用复数。

ex.enText: When the air becomes hot, its volume increases rapidly.
ex.chText: 空气变热时，其体积便迅速膨胀。

ex.enText: The volume of this box is 180 cubic feet.
ex.chText: 这个箱子的容积为180立方英尺。

ex.enText: The volume of business with Brazil has increased.
ex.chText: 与巴西的贸易额增加了。

synonyms.bx: 指某物的体积或某容器的容积或容量，也可指生产、贸易、销售等的数量或数额。

data.enText: to make sth bigger, thicker or heavier
data.chText: 使某物加大（或加厚、加重）

data.enText: to be the most important part of sth

tr: the property possessed by a large mass
the property of something that is great in magnitude
example: it is cheaper to buy it in bulk
he received a mass of correspondence

tr: the property resulting from being or relating to the greater in number of two parts
example: the majority of his customers prefer it
the bulk of the work is finished

tr: cause to bulge or swell outwards

example: The parcel bulked in the sack

example.ex: The truck pulled out of the lot, its bulk unnerving against the dawn.
example.tran: 卡车从空地上开出来，庞大的车身小心翼翼地避让着草坪。

example.ex: ...the shadowy bulk of an ancient barn.
example.tran: 一座古老谷仓的巨大阴影

value.def: You can refer to something's bulk when you want to emphasize that it is very large.

example.ex: Bannol lowered his bulk carefully into the chair...
example.tran: 班诺尔小心翼翼地将肥硕的身躯落座到椅子上。

example.ex: Despite his bulk he moved lightly on his feet.
example.tran: 尽管他身形庞大，移动起来还是很灵巧。

value.def: You can refer to a large person's body or to their weight or size as their bulk .
value.tran: 庞大的身躯；巨大的体重；肥硕的体形

example.ex: The bulk of the text is essentially a review of these original documents...
example.tran: 文章的主要部分基本是对这些原始文件的回顾。

example.ex: The vast bulk of imports and exports are carried by sea.
example.tran: 大部分的进出口货物都是通过海路运输的。

example.ex: They come from all over the world, though the bulk is from the Indian subcontinent.
example.tran: 他们来自世界各地，但大多数还是来自印度次大陆。

value.def: The bulk of something is most of it.

example.ex: Buying in bulk is more economical than shopping for small quantities.
example.tran: 批量采购要比零买实惠很多。

value.def: If you buy or sell something in bulk, you buy or sell it in large quantities.

trans: 散装货称；大宗货物（参见cargo in bulk）；缩写词为b/c，B．C．，BC
堆密度；松密度；容积密度，容重
大货生产；成批生产；大货
土壤容重；土壤密度；土壤容量；土壤体积质量
